00:12:08,645 --> 00:12:10,230
I mean, the two of
you have been close

253
00:12:10,271 --> 00:12:12,690
pretty much your whole
lives, haven't you?

254
00:12:15,068 --> 00:12:16,527
[KAGURA]
That's true.

255
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:19,447
I first met him
when we were kids.

256
00:12:19,489 --> 00:12:22,158
He was drawing a fried
egg in the dirt.

257
00:12:23,660 --> 00:12:25,954
A fried egg?

258
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:27,580
[KAGURA]
Yeah.

259
00:12:30,959 --> 00:12:33,086
[KAGURA]
Hiya.

260
00:12:33,127 --> 00:12:36,130
If you want someone to
play with you, I will.

261
00:12:36,172 --> 00:12:37,924
You mean it?

262
00:12:37,966 --> 00:12:41,219
Yeah! Of course!

263
00:12:41,261 --> 00:12:44,514
And from now on,
I'll stay by your side.

264
00:12:44,555 --> 00:12:47,392
You and I will be
together forever!

265
00:12:54,065 --> 00:12:56,276
[TOHRU]
That look...

266
00:12:56,317 --> 00:12:58,653
I can tell you've
always liked him.

267
00:13:00,530 --> 00:13:03,992
Hey, Tohru. I wanna thank you.

268
00:13:06,077 --> 00:13:08,204
[KAGURA]
For coming to find me.

269
00:13:13,084 --> 00:13:14,711
Come on, we should get home.

270
00:13:14,752 --> 00:13:17,714
I bet everyone's gotta
be starving by now.

271
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:20,466
Yeah.

272
00:13:20,508 --> 00:13:21,759
[TOHRU]
So, what're you gonna make?

273
00:13:21,801 --> 00:13:23,553
[KAGURA] I was thinking
hamburger steaks.

274
00:13:23,594 --> 00:13:25,221
[TOHRU]
I'd love to help, if you want.

275
00:13:25,263 --> 00:13:26,514
[KAGURA]
Yes, please do!

276
00:13:26,556 --> 00:13:29,100
[TOHRU]
My mouth is already watering.

277
00:13:29,142 --> 00:13:31,019
[stomach growling]

278
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:33,938
It's possible I might starve.

279
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:35,523
Same.

280
00:13:35,565 --> 00:13:36,983
‐‐[TOHRU] Hi, everyone.
‐‐[KAGURA] We're home.

281
00:13:37,025 --> 00:13:38,568
And we're saved.

282
00:13:38,609 --> 00:13:39,986
Welcome back, girls.

283
00:13:40,028 --> 00:13:42,447
We'll get dinner together
as fast as we can.

284
00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:45,116
I'll follow your lead.
Let's not waste any time, 'kay?

285
00:13:45,158 --> 00:13:46,576
Right!

286
00:13:46,617 --> 00:13:48,828
[TOHRU, YUKI giggle]

287
00:13:56,419 --> 00:13:57,962
'Kay, these are almost ready.

288
00:13:58,004 --> 00:13:59,839
Could you go ahead and
set the table maybe?

289
00:13:59,881 --> 00:14:01,716
I'm already on it.

290
00:14:05,136 --> 00:14:06,637
Dinner's about to be served.

291
00:14:06,679 --> 00:14:08,681
Smells heavenly.

292
00:14:08,723 --> 00:14:09,932
Where'd Kyo go?

293
00:14:09,974 --> 00:14:13,394
[YUKI] He went upstairs a while
ago and hasn't come down yet.

294
00:14:16,189 --> 00:14:19,359
Hey, Kyo! It's almost
time to eat dinner.

295
00:14:24,572 --> 00:14:26,574
Ah, there you are.

296
00:14:26,616 --> 00:14:29,160
I should've known
I'd find you up here.

297
00:14:29,202 --> 00:14:31,662
The food'll be done in a minute.

298
00:14:31,704 --> 00:14:33,456
I'm gonna pass.

299
00:14:33,498 --> 00:14:36,417
Kagura worked really hard
to put it together, though.

300
00:14:36,459 --> 00:14:38,878
She said she just wants
to make you happy.

301
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:41,297
[KYO] Yeah, well, she's always
saying crazy things.

302
00:14:41,339 --> 00:14:43,508
Like all that marriage stuff.

303
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:45,676
There must be something
wrong with her brain.

304
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:47,428
It's so annoying.

305
00:14:47,470 --> 00:14:48,304
[TOHRU]
But...

306
00:14:48,346 --> 00:14:51,265
Isn't it a blessing to have
someone care about you?

307
00:14:51,307 --> 00:14:53,559
Someone who worries
about your happiness

308
00:14:53,601 --> 00:14:56,396
and wants to always
be by your side?

309
00:14:56,437 --> 00:14:59,732
You know, I'd like to think
someone cares for me that way.

310
00:14:59,774 --> 00:15:03,403
Even if that person and I are
separated by a huge distance.

311
00:15:03,444 --> 00:15:06,197
I find it very reassuring.

312
00:15:06,239 --> 00:15:07,657
And it's amazing to me

313
00:15:07,698 --> 00:15:09,534
the way someone can
love another person

314
00:15:09,575 --> 00:15:12,036
with their entire heart.

315
00:15:12,078 --> 00:15:14,247
'Cause after all,
doesn't everybody dream

316
00:15:14,288 --> 00:15:16,999
there's someone out there
destined to be with them?

317
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:20,670
Uh... I don't know about that.

318
00:15:20,711 --> 00:15:22,130
I know what you dream of.

319
00:15:22,171 --> 00:15:24,090
You wanna defeat
Soma, don't you?

320
00:15:24,132 --> 00:15:27,385
That's why you went into
the mountains to train.

321
00:15:27,427 --> 00:15:30,847
Ugh. Shigure's been blabbing.

322
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:33,015
[TOHRU] That training must
have been hard on you.

323
00:15:33,057 --> 00:15:35,601
Especially since you were
by yourself out there.

324
00:15:35,643 --> 00:15:38,855
[KYO] I wasn't alone. I had
my master there with me.

325
00:15:38,896 --> 00:15:40,106
[TOHRU]
Oh, I didn't know.

326
00:15:40,148 --> 00:15:42,400
Is he a very strong person?

327
00:15:42,442 --> 00:15:44,402
Obviously, he has to be!

328
00:15:44,444 --> 00:15:47,822
He's an amazing fighter.
Even Yuki couldn't beat the guy.

329
00:15:47,864 --> 00:15:50,783
He's been teaching me since
I was just a little kid.

330
00:15:50,825 --> 00:15:52,702
Which is why I've
gotten so strong.

331
00:15:52,743 --> 00:15:54,787
Plus, even though he's a
member of the Soma clan,

332
00:15:54,829 --> 00:15:56,831
he actually understands me.

333
00:15:56,873 --> 00:15:58,958
You wouldn't believe
how tough he is.

334
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,711
I could hardly wait for
our lessons each morning.

335
00:16:01,752 --> 00:16:03,921
Don't get me wrong,
the training was harsh,

336
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:06,507
but it was also
incredibly fulfilling.

337
00:16:06,549 --> 00:16:09,177
I felt myself getting stronger.

338
00:16:09,218 --> 00:16:12,346
Just thinking about it
gets me so pumped up.

339
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:14,515
[TOHRU]
I've never seen him so excited.

340
00:16:14,557 --> 00:16:16,392
He's got so much passion.

341
00:16:16,434 --> 00:16:20,438
[KYO] Man, I could really go for
a few sparring rounds right now.

342
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:23,274
[TOHRU] It's not that he
just wants to beat Soma.

343
00:16:23,316 --> 00:16:26,277
He truly loves martial arts.

344
00:16:26,319 --> 00:16:27,195
[KYO gasps]

345
00:16:27,236 --> 00:16:30,531
Oh. This is probably boring
to a girl like you, I bet?

346
00:16:30,573 --> 00:16:31,782
What? No way!

347
00:16:31,824 --> 00:16:33,910
Okay, sure, I don't know
much about martial arts,

348
00:16:33,951 --> 00:16:34,869
but I'm not bored at all!

349
00:16:34,911 --> 00:16:37,163
I promise! This is
really interesting!

350
00:16:37,205 --> 00:16:39,457
Yeah? 'Cause I'd be
bored in your shoes.

351
00:16:39,499 --> 00:16:41,584
It's not like you care
about this stuff.

352
00:16:41,626 --> 00:16:43,336
True, I do have trouble
not falling asleep

353
00:16:43,377 --> 00:16:45,004
when people are talking
about, like, physics,

354
00:16:45,046 --> 00:16:47,256
but I'm not completely
uninterested in martial arts.

355
00:16:47,298 --> 00:16:48,633
I even know a few moves!

356
00:16:48,674 --> 00:16:49,634
Like, let me think!

357
00:16:49,675 --> 00:16:54,263
There's the, uh, um, what's
it called? Right‐handed jab!

358
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:01,145
Horrible.

359
00:17:04,357 --> 00:17:06,025
[TOHRU] I feel like I've
caught another glimpse

360
00:17:06,067 --> 00:17:08,861
of the true Kyo.

361
00:17:08,903 --> 00:17:12,323
Underneath that grumpy look,
he always has on his face,

362
00:17:12,365 --> 00:17:15,201
he's hiding an awkward smile.

363
00:17:19,497 --> 00:17:21,082
Thank you for waiting.

364
00:17:21,123 --> 00:17:23,960
[SHIGURE] You took so long, I
thought I was going to pass out.

365
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:26,003
Sorry 'bout that.

366
00:17:26,045 --> 00:17:27,255
[KAGURA]
Here.

367
00:17:30,841 --> 00:17:33,928
This one's yours.

368
00:17:38,099 --> 00:17:39,725
[SHIGURE]
What's this?

369
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:42,645
Now why did Kyo get a
fried egg on top of his?

370
00:17:42,687 --> 00:17:45,565
Looks good. Let's eat
it before it gets cold.

371
00:17:45,606 --> 00:17:46,399
[SHIGURE]
Thanks for the food!

372
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:48,484
‐‐[YUKI] Thank you for the food.
‐‐[TOHRU] Thank you, Kagura.

373
00:17:48,526 --> 00:17:50,236
This is delicious.

374
00:17:50,278 --> 00:17:52,154
It really is.

375
00:17:54,699 --> 00:17:57,243
My tastebuds are so happy.

376
00:18:10,381 --> 00:18:13,384
What are you waiting for?
Have a seat and join us!

377
00:18:13,426 --> 00:18:15,094
Sure.

378
00:18:15,136 --> 00:18:16,470
[SHIGURE]
It's getting late, Kagura.

379
00:18:16,512 --> 00:18:18,514
It would probably be best
if you stayed the night.

380
00:18:18,556 --> 00:18:21,851
[KAGURA] Really? Yay!
Let's share a bed, Kyo.

381
00:18:21,892 --> 00:18:23,102
[KYO]
Not on your life!

382
00:18:23,144 --> 00:18:25,521
[KAGURA]
Aw, no need to be shy.

383
00:18:29,275 --> 00:18:31,193
[KAGURA]
Today we must part.

384
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:34,280
Please be well, my love.
I'll come back to see you soon.

385
00:18:34,322 --> 00:18:37,658
I'll be fine as long as you stay
as far away from me as possible!

386
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:39,869
Well, they're in high
spirits this morning.

387
00:18:39,910 --> 00:18:41,329
So, what's your guess?

388
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:43,581
Did you figure out
Kagura's year?

389
00:18:43,623 --> 00:18:45,750
No, I didn't.

390
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:46,250
[BOTH]
Huh?

391
00:18:46,292 --> 00:18:50,254
Fine! Just for that, you're not
even getting a kiss goodbye!

392
00:18:50,296 --> 00:18:53,174
I'm not going to take any
more of your punches‐‐

393
00:18:54,467 --> 00:18:56,385
[SHIGURE]
My TV!

394
00:18:56,427 --> 00:19:00,389
I can't believe him.
How can he be so mean?

395
00:19:00,431 --> 00:19:02,516
But... I love him!

396
00:19:02,558 --> 00:19:04,185
‐‐[SHIGURE, KYO] Who's that?
‐‐Someone's there!

397
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:10,691
Oh, good morning.
How can I help you, sir?

398
00:19:10,733 --> 00:19:13,903
Oh, I, uh... forgot
to deliver your paper.

399
00:19:13,944 --> 00:19:15,988
Thank you!

400
00:19:16,030 --> 00:19:17,657
[SHIGURE]
Perfect save.

401
00:19:17,698 --> 00:19:19,825
[TOHRU] Soma's even more
dazzling than usual

402
00:19:19,867 --> 00:19:20,660
this morning.

403
00:19:20,701 --> 00:19:24,455
That was a close one.
Be more careful, Kagura.

404
00:19:24,497 --> 00:19:25,623
[KAGURA]
Sorry.

405
00:19:25,665 --> 00:19:26,540
[gasps]

406
00:19:26,582 --> 00:19:27,917
[KAGURA]
I didn't know there'd be a man

407
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:30,127
on the other side of the door.

408
00:19:30,169 --> 00:19:31,962
Okay, I figured out her year.

409
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:34,632
It turns out her zodiac
is the Year of the Boar.

410
00:19:34,674 --> 00:19:37,468
[SHIGURE] I don't think this
counts as "figuring it out."

411
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:40,221
And yet, you seem so
pleased with yourself.

412
00:19:40,262 --> 00:19:41,722
This makes perfect sense.

413
00:19:41,764 --> 00:19:44,225
When you have a goal,
it's all you can think about.

414
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:46,977
This must be the Boar's
influence on you.

415
00:19:47,019 --> 00:19:49,438
[SHIGURE] That's less of a
deduction and more of a fact.

416
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:50,898
I've gotta hug you.

417
00:19:50,940 --> 00:19:53,859
You're the cutest little piggy
I could ever imagine.

418
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:55,319
She's ignoring me.

419
00:19:55,361 --> 00:19:58,030
Hey, Kagura. I think
I kinda see now.

420
00:19:58,072 --> 00:19:59,448
At first, I didn't understand

421
00:19:59,490 --> 00:20:01,826
what could make you
love Kyo so much.

422
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:03,035
But after last night,

423
00:20:03,077 --> 00:20:06,539
I can tell there are a bunch
of great things about him.

424
00:20:06,580 --> 00:20:08,249
I hope I can see more of them...

425
00:20:08,290 --> 00:20:11,502
How dare you cheat on me!

426
00:20:11,544 --> 00:20:12,294
I knew it!

427
00:20:12,336 --> 00:20:14,755
I can't take my eyes off of
you for a single second!

428
00:20:14,797 --> 00:20:16,298
[KYO]
What are you talking about?

429
00:20:16,340 --> 00:20:18,509
I thought you said you'd
forgive his affairs.

430
00:20:18,551 --> 00:20:21,178
I never said he wouldn't
be punished first!

431
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:22,513
[TOHRU]
Excuse me.

432
00:20:22,555 --> 00:20:24,640
I think there's a
misunderstanding.

433
00:20:24,682 --> 00:20:26,934
I meant that I wanna become
someone more like you,

434
00:20:26,976 --> 00:20:28,519
who's able to see
the good in people

435
00:20:28,561 --> 00:20:30,479
even when it isn't obvious.

436
00:20:30,521 --> 00:20:32,022
Does that make sense?

437
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:33,065
[gasps]

438
00:20:33,107 --> 00:20:35,735
You mean it? Like, for real?

439
00:20:35,776 --> 00:20:39,613
Yeah! I think it's a fantastic
trait to have, don't you?

440
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:40,865
[gasps]

441
00:20:42,825 --> 00:20:44,118
Yeah, I do.

442
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:46,036
Put some clothes on!

443
00:20:46,078 --> 00:20:48,914
You need more training, dummy.

444
00:20:50,708 --> 00:20:53,586
[KAGURA]
See ya later, darling!

445
00:20:53,627 --> 00:20:55,588
Let's get together real soon!

446
00:20:55,629 --> 00:20:58,299
[KYO]
Hurricane Kagura has passed.

447
00:20:58,340 --> 00:20:59,467
Darn it.

448
00:20:59,508 --> 00:21:02,845
With all this chaos at home,
I didn't get to plant anything.

449
00:21:02,887 --> 00:21:03,637
[TOHRU gasps]

450
00:21:03,679 --> 00:21:05,222
So, are you going to
grow something new

451
00:21:05,264 --> 00:21:06,932
at your secret base?

452
00:21:06,974 --> 00:21:08,517
Yeah, strawberries.

453
00:21:08,559 --> 00:21:12,354
Really? I love strawberries.

454
00:21:12,396 --> 00:21:14,690
I'd hoped you might like them.

455
00:21:17,693 --> 00:21:19,528
We're gonna be late.

456
00:21:25,367 --> 00:21:31,123
[TOHRU] For some reason, I have
way more motivation lately.

457
00:21:31,165 --> 00:21:32,458
[TOHRU]
I'll take these.

458
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:35,419
[LIBRARIAN A]
All right. One moment.

459
00:21:35,461 --> 00:21:36,962
[TOHRU] I wanna learn
more about the things

460
00:21:37,004 --> 00:21:39,256
that Kyo and Soma
are interested in.

461
00:21:39,298 --> 00:21:41,634
And what they dislike, too!

462
00:21:41,675 --> 00:21:45,179
If I do that, then maybe...

463
00:21:45,221 --> 00:21:46,806
...maybe I'll get to
see more of the sides

464
00:21:46,847 --> 00:21:49,141
that they keep hidden
from the world.

465
00:21:49,183 --> 00:21:51,435
At least, I hope that happens.

466
00:21:51,477 --> 00:21:53,479
[MAYUKO]
Oh, there you are.

467
00:21:53,521 --> 00:21:56,732
Honda. There's a call for
you in the staff room.

468
00:21:59,735 --> 00:22:04,281
[TOHRU] Hello? I hope you
weren't waiting long.

469
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:06,492
Grandpa?

470
00:22:06,534 --> 00:22:07,868
[gasps]

471
00:22:13,499 --> 00:22:15,918
[TOHRU]
I'd gotten too comfortable.

472
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:18,295
I knew my living
situation was temporary

473
00:22:18,337 --> 00:22:22,216
and that one day
I'd have to leave...

474
00:22:22,258 --> 00:22:26,053
Yet, somehow, I managed to
fool myself into believing

475
00:22:26,095 --> 00:22:29,515
that the Somas and I
could be a family.

476
00:24:04,610 --> 00:24:07,071
[TOHRU]
"I've been fooling myself."

